# ABOUTME: Release changelog for the Protobuf distribution (CPAN::Changes format).
Revision history for Protobuf

{{$NEXT}}
          - Renamed the distribution and namespace from Proto3 to Protobuf
            (Proto3::* -> Protobuf::*; bin/proto3-* -> bin/protobuf-*). The
            library covers the whole format, not the proto3 dialect, so the
            name now reflects that.
          - Full protobuf v34 conformance: proto2, proto3, and editions 2023,
            both Required and Recommended (--enforce_recommended), zero
            failures. Adds proto2 (explicit presence, required fields,
            defaults, groups, extensions, MessageSet, closed enums, expanded
            repeated) and editions support via a resolved feature model.
          - CI runs the prebuilt v34 conformance runner as a blocking gate on
            every push and pull request, uploading the full result as an
            artifact.

0.1.0     2026-06-01
          - Initial release.
          - Pure-Perl proto3 wire codec: scalars, messages, enums, repeated,
            packed, maps, oneofs, and unknown-field preservation.
          - Hand-written .proto parser (lexer + grammar) with transitive import
            following and import-cycle detection.
          - Cross-file type resolver with innermost-first scope resolution,
            verified byte-for-byte against protoc.
          - Canonical proto3 JSON mapping, both directions.
          - Well-known types: Timestamp, Duration, Any, Struct/Value/ListValue/
            NullValue, FieldMask, Empty, and the scalar wrappers.
          - Runtime class generation from a schema.
          - Ahead-of-time code generation with deterministic, byte-identical
            output.
          - FileDescriptorSet loading.
          - Conformance testee plus a skip-aware harness that drives Google's
            conformance_test_runner in CI.
          - Zero install-time XS; requires Perl 5.38+.
